# The Simple X Hotkey Daemon is the program used by LARBS to map most of the
# dwm-independent commands.  This file is pretty readable, so I'll let you read
# it.

# The keys NOT bound here by sxhkd, but by dwm or i3 are:
# The t thru p keys on the top row
# The f thru ; keys on the home row
# The b key on the bottom row (hides the bar in either case)
# Function Keys
XF86AudioMute
	amixer -q sset Master toggle; pkill -RTMIN+10 blocks
XF86Audio{Raise,Lower}Volume
	amixer -q sset Master 5%{+,-} unmute; pkill -RTMIN+10 blocks
XF86AudioMicMute
	amixer -q sset Capture toggle; pkill -RTMIN+10 blocks
XF86MonBrightness{Down,Up}
	xbacklight -{dec,inc} 5
#XF86Display
#termite -e nmtui-connect?
#XF86WLAN
#
XF86Tools
	pkill -USR1 '^redshift$'
alt + Tab
	rofi -show window
#XF86Bluetooth
#
#XF86Favorites
# emacs config?
